{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted"]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Cloud-File-System","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem"],"title":"Cloud File System"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/VaultInfo"],"title":"Structures"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionError","doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionFormat","doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/FileEncryptor"],"title":"Enumerations"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"EnsemblesEncrypted"}],"symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","role":"collection","title":"EnsemblesEncrypted","externalID":"EnsemblesEncrypted"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EnsemblesEncrypted provides "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", a wrapper that encrypts files before uploading and decrypts after downloading. It can wrap any ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CloudFileSystem"},{"text":" implementation — CloudKit, Google Drive, WebDAV, or your own custom backend — to provide end-to-end encryption for sync data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Encrypted files are stored in a password-derived vault directory with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"text":" extension. This is backward compatible with the Ensembles 2 Objective-C ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEEncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Encryption-Formats","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Encryption Formats"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two encryption formats are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".modern"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" (default) — AES-256-GCM. Fast, authenticated encryption using Apple’s CryptoKit. Recommended for new apps."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — RNCryptor v3 format. Use this for backward compatibility with Ensembles 2 encrypted data."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The backend auto-detects the encryption format when downloading, so a "},{"code":".modern","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" client can read "},{"code":".legacy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" files and vice versa. The format setting only controls how "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"new","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" files are encrypted."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Setup","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Setup"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Wrap any cloud file system with encryption:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesEncrypted","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","\/\/ Wrap CloudKit with encryption","let cloudKitFS = CloudKitFileSystem(","    ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.yourcompany.yourapp\"",")","let encryptedFS = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: cloudKitFS,","    password: \"user-supplied-password\"",")","","let ensemble = CoreDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MainStore\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    managedObjectModelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: encryptedFS!",")","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more control over the vault, use the "},{"code":"VaultInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let encryptedFS = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: innerFS,","    vaultInfo: vaultInfo,","    encryptionFormat: .modern",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"When-to-Use-Encryption","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"When to Use Encryption"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles sync data is stored as opaque binary files, so even without encryption the raw data is not human-readable. However, it could be deserialized by someone with access to your cloud storage."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CloudKit","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":", Apple encrypts "},{"code":"CKAsset","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" data at rest. With Advanced Data Protection (ADP) enabled, assets are end-to-end encrypted. Wrapping CloudKit with "},{"code":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" adds a layer of protection that doesn’t depend on the user enabling ADP."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"third-party backends","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" (Google Drive, OneDrive, WebDAV, etc.), the storage provider can see the raw files. Wrapping with "},{"code":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" ensures data is encrypted before it leaves the device, regardless of what the provider does."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-It-Works","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"How It Works"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Vault directory"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — All encrypted files are stored inside a vault directory in the cloud, derived from the password. Different passwords create different vaults, so the same cloud account can host multiple independent encrypted sync stores."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upload"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — When Ensembles uploads a file, the wrapper encrypts it to a local temporary file, uploads the encrypted version with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"type":"text","text":" extension, then removes the temporary file."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Download"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — When Ensembles downloads a file, the wrapper downloads the encrypted "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".cdecrypt"},{"type":"text","text":" file, auto-detects the format (modern or legacy), decrypts it to a local temporary file, and returns the decrypted content."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Backward compatibility"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legacy"},{"type":"text","text":" format uses RNCryptor v3, the same encryption format used by Ensembles 2’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CDEEncryptedCloudFileSystem"},{"type":"text","text":". Apps migrating from E2 to E3 can read existing encrypted cloud data without re-encrypting."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Wrapping-Other-Backends","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Wrapping Other Backends"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wrapper works with any "},{"code":"CloudFileSystem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Wrap Google Drive","let encryptedGDrive = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: GoogleDriveCloudFileSystem(authenticator: gdAuthenticator),","    password: password",")","","\/\/ Wrap WebDAV","let encryptedWebDAV = EncryptedCloudFileSystem(","    cloudFileSystem: WebDAVCloudFileSystem(baseURL: webdavURL, username: user, password: pass),","    password: encryptionPassword",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Dependencies","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Dependencies"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This module has "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"no external dependencies","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" beyond Foundation, CryptoKit, and the core "},{"code":"Ensembles","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" framework."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An encryption wrapper for any Ensembles cloud backend."}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An encryption wrapper for any Ensembles cloud backend."}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted","title":"EnsemblesEncrypted","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/FileEncryptor":{"abstract":[{"text":"Unified encryption\/decryption interface with automatic format detection on decrypt.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"FileEncryptor","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/FileEncryptor","title":"FileEncryptor","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/fileencryptor","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FileEncryptor","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptedCloudFileSystem":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A cloud file system wrapper that encrypts files before uploading"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and decrypts them after downloading.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptedcloudfilesystem","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptedCloudFileSystem","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"EncryptedCloudFileSystem"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptionFormat":{"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptionformat","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The encryption format to use when encrypting data."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EncryptionFormat"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EncryptionFormat"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionFormat","role":"symbol","title":"EncryptionFormat","type":"topic"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/VaultInfo":{"url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/vaultinfo","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VaultInfo"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Represents a vault in an encrypted cloud file system.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VaultInfo"}],"title":"VaultInfo","identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/VaultInfo"},"doc://EnsemblesEncrypted/documentation/EnsemblesEncrypted/EncryptionError":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Errors that can occur during encryption or decryption.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/documentation\/EnsemblesEncrypted\/EncryptionError","title":"EncryptionError","url":"\/documentation\/ensemblesencrypted\/encryptionerror","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EncryptionError","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"EncryptionError","kind":"identifier"}]}}}